{{Advanced Placement}}

'''AP Russian Language and Culture''' is a proposed [[Advanced Placement]] course and examination, in development since 2005.<ref name="APPG2005">{{cite web|url=http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/repository/ap05_programguide_46836.pdf|title=AP Program Guide, 2005–06|publisher=The College Board|accessdate=August 10, 2014}}</ref> It is being developed through the [[American Council of Teachers of Russian]], in collaboration with the [[College Board]] and with funding from the [[U.S. Department of Education]] and the [[National Security Education Program]].<ref name="CBAPRHome">{{cite web|deadurl=yes |title=AP Russian Language and Culture Course Home Page |publisher=College Board |url=http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/37220.html |archivedate=January 13, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070113231114/http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/37220.html |accessdate=August 10, 2013 }}</ref>

AP Russian Language is equivalent to a second-year college-level [[Russian language]] course. Students enrolling in AP Russian Language and Culture are typically in their fourth or fifth year of language study, or have had equivalent experience with the language.{{cn|date=August 2014}}

The exam is reported with a score of 1 to 5. A prototype exam was administered to students in 2010.<ref name="Marshall RLJ">{{cite journal|last=Marshall|first=Camelot|title=Examining the Validity of the 2010 Prototype AP Russian Exam through a College Comparability Study|journal=Russian Language Journal|volume=60|pages=319–331|url=http://rlj.americancouncils.org/issues/60/files/Marshall_2010.pdf|accessdate=August 10, 2014}}</ref>

